  "prompt": "How do I delete my own question from Quora?",
  "response": "To delete your own question on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the Question**: Navigate to the question you want to delete by clicking on it.\n\n2. **Click on the Three Dots (\u2022\u2022\u2022)**  \n   At the top-right corner of the question, you\u2019ll see three dots. Click on them to open the options menu.\n\n3. **Select \"Delete\"**  \n   From the dropdown menu, select the **Delete** option.\n\n4. **Confirm Deletion**  \n   A confirmation prompt will appear asking if you\u2019re sure you want to delete the question. Click **Delete** to confirm.\n\n### Notes:\n- Once a question is deleted, it cannot be recovered.\n- If your question has answers from other users, those answers will also be deleted permanently.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
